Here are the breaking changes and fixes for your code when upgrading to `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 (which uses `Microsoft.OpenApi` v2.x):

---

### 1. `OpenApiAny`/`OpenApiString` → `JsonNode`

The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace (`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, `OpenApiObject`, etc.) was removed. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` instead:

```diff
- using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
+ using System.Text.Json.Nodes;

- param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");
+ param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` → `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`

Entities are now typed as interfaces (`IOpenApiSecurityScheme`). Use the concrete reference type instead of setting `Reference` manually:

```diff
- var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
- {
-     Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
- };
+ var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

### 3. `schema.Nullable` removed

OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema's `type` array with `"null"`. The `Nullable` property no longer exists:

```diff
- property.Value.Nullable = false;
+ // Remove — nullable is now expressed via the type array.
+ // To make non-nullable, ensure JsonSchemaType.Null is NOT in the type:
+ property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

(Use `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;` — `JsonSchemaType` lives there.)

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401",
        new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = ... }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
